\documentfinalizeafter=5pm,think triangulation=1 gave up.folding after a year of existence. This is the final presentation from the 18 member MMM (Initiative for Triangular Modelling) team that was set up in 2012 to design and build a geometric representation of time. My role was to develop and compose the visual aspects, including the sounds and text. The final product was a 3D interactive audio-visual installation of triangular area and timeline sequences, with a click anywhere interface and scene changes under the control of a matrix. Its function was to create a 3D dynamic environment in which to think about time as a dimension of space and a space for time. This is my commentary on my role and the trajectory of the project since I left in 2014. Deliberately not included are things I did because of my prior role or changed priorities. Deliberately included are things I did but now consider or want to re-do for the experience has value for me regardless of changed circumstances. \newif\ifshowtrims \showtrims=false \trims=false\ifshowtrims 
